{"title_page": "Subedar Joginder Singh (film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 Indian Punjabi language biographical war film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}}\n{{refimprove|date=September 2017}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name = Subedar Joginder Singh\n| image = Subedar Joginder Singh - Poster.jpg\n| caption = \n| director = [[Simerjit Singh]]\n| producer = Sumeet Singh\n| screenplay = Raashid Rangrez<br />Simerjit Singh\n| story = Raashid Rangrez<br />Simerjit Singh\n| based on = [[Subedar Joginder Singh]]\n| starring = [[Gippy Grewal]]<br>[[Aditi Sharma]]<br>[[Guggu Gill]]<br>[[Kulwinder Billa]]<br>[[Karamjit Anmol]]<br>Rajvir Jawanda <br>Sardar Sohi\n| music = <small>'''Songs'''</small><br>Jassi Katyal<br>Jaidev Kumar<br>Gurmeet Singh<br><small>'''Background Music'''</small><br>Amar Mohile\n| cinematography = Navneet Misser\n| editing = Bunty Nagi\n| studio = Seven Colors Motion Pictures<br>Unisys Infosolutions Pvt Ltd\n| released = {{Film date|2018|04|06|df=y}}\n| country = India\n| language = Punjabi\n| budget= <!--Must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb.-->\n| gross= <!--Must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb.-->\n}}\n\n'''''Subedar Joginder Singh''''' is a 2018 Indian [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]]-language [[biographical]] [[war film]] based on the life of [[Joginder Singh (soldier)|Joginder Singh]], an Indian soldier who was killed in the 1962 [[Sino-Indian War]] and posthumously awarded the [[Param Vir Chakra]]. It is produced by Saga Music and is set to release by 6 April 2018<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/gippy-grewal-even-if-i-do-only-one-hindi-film-a-year-it-should-be-brilliant/articleshow/60529767.cms|title=Gippy Grewal: Even if I do only one Hindi film a year, it should be brilliant - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2017-09-19}}</ref>. The film stars [[Gippy Grewal]] and [[Aditi Sharma]] and is directed by [[Simerjit Singh]] who belongs to the same region of Moga where Subedar was born.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ani/gippy-grewal-all-set-to-star-in-war-biopic-subedar-joginder-singh-117062100952_1.html|title=Gippy Grewal all set to star in war biopic 'Subedar Joginder Singh'|last=ANI|date=2017-06-21|work=Business Standard India|access-date=2017-09-19}}</ref>. This movie is going to be high budget film as the dialogues and picturization is anticipated to be authentic to that in the era of 1962<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/gippy-grewal-to-play-subedar-joginder-singh/articleshow/59233506.cms|title=Gippy Grewal to play Subedar Joginder Singh - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2017-09-21}}</ref>.\n\nThe first schedule of the movie was shot in Suratgarh or Rajasthan which is nearly 100&nbsp;km from the Indo-Pakistan border, to give a look of pre-independence village of Punjab. The next schedule of the shooting is lined up in early October 2017 at [[Dras]] sector in [[Jammu and Kashmir]] to give real life experience of the Tawang valley during the [[Sino-Indian War|1962 Indo-China war]].\n\n== Plot ==\nThis movie is based upon the life, struggle and valor of a Subedar in Indian Army who achieved his martyrdom while fighting Chinese in Indo-China war of 1962. This movie is believed to depict Subedar's professional and personal life and how he handled while serving his nation.\n\n== Cast ==\n* [[Gippy Grewal]] as Subedar Joginder Singh\n* [[Aditi Sharma]] as Gurdyal Kaur\n* [[Nirmal Rishi]] as Joginder Singh's Mother  \n* [[Guggu Gill]] as Maan Singh\n* [[Kulwinder Billa]] as Ajaib Singh (Sipahi)\n* [[Roshan Prince]] as Swaran Singh (Sipahi)\n* [[Jaggi Singh (actor)|Jaggi Singh]] as Santokh Singh (Sipahi)\n* [[Jordan Sandhu]] as Bant Singh\n* [[Karamjit Anmol]] as Bawa Singh (Sipahi) \n* Rajvir Jawanda as Bahadur Singh (Sipahi)\n* [[Harish Verma]] as Commander\n* Parminder Gill as Mother in law\n* Harpreet Singh as Sepoy\n* Sharan Maan as Bhaag Singh (Sipahi)\n\n==Shooting locations==\n\n[[Suratgarh]] is a small town in [[Sri Ganganagar]] district of [[Rajasthan]] and is in the close proximity of [[Radcliffe Line]] <nowiki/>demarcated between [[wikipedia:India|India]] and [[wikipedia:Pakistan|Pakistan]]. [[Suratgarh]] is also famous for its [[Suratgarh Air Force Station|Air Force Base Station]] which provide strategic advantage to [[wikipedia:India|India]] over neighboring [[wikipedia:Pakistan|Pakistan]]. It has been chosen for the shooting the first schedule of the film because of resemblance with the village of [[Punjab, India|Punjab]] in undivided India back in 1921 where [[Joginder Singh Sahnan|Subedar Joginder Singh]] lived his childhood and adolescence till he joined [[British Indian Army]].\n\n[[Dras]], a beauteous town on [[National Highway 1D (India, old numbering)|National Highway 1D]] or popularly known as [[Srinagar-Leh Highway]] came into prominence owing to [[Pakistanis|Pakistani]] incursions in [[Kargil|Kargil sector]] in the summers of 1999, but it is also the second coldest inhabited place in the world. Second schedule is going on in the treacherous terrain of Dras and will wrapped up by the end of October 2017.\n\n==Soundtrack==\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Subedar Joginder Singh\n| type       = soundtrack\n| artist     = Jassi Katyal, Gurmeet Singh & Jaidev Kumar\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{Start date|df=yes|2018|04|05}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/subedar-joginder-singh-original-motion-picture-soundtrack/1368435104 |title=Subedar Joginder Singh (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack) |publisher=[[iTunes]]}}</ref>\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = 26:35\n| la